Package mlflex.ensemblelearners

Class Summary
AbstractEnsembleLearner ML-Flex supports ensemble-learning approaches for aggregating evidence from multiple classification predictions.
AbstractWeightedVoteEnsembleLearner Several of the ensemblelearners/combiner approaches in ML-Flex have a common characteristic: they assign weights to individual predictions before making the combined prediction.
MajorityVoteEnsembleLearner This class represents an ensemble/combiner approach that forms an aggregate prediction based on a majority vote on the individual predictions.
MaxProbabilityEnsembleLearner This class represents an ensemblelearners/combiner approach that computes the combined prediction according to the class probabilities that were assigned for each individual prediction.
MeanProbabilityEnsembleLearner This class represents an ensemblelearners/combiner approach that computes the combined prediction according to the class probabilities that were assigned for each individual prediction.
SelectBestEnsembleLearner This class represents an ensemblelearners/combiner approach that computes the combined prediction according to the performance attained in the inner cross-validation folds.
StackedEnsembleLearner This class implements the "stacked combiner" approach ensemblelearners learning.
WeightedMeanProbabilityEnsembleLearner This class represents an ensemblelearners/combiner approach that computes the combined prediction according to the class probabilities that were assigned for each individual prediction.
WeightedVoteEnsembleLearner This weight-based ensemblelearners-learning approaches uses the weight assigned to each individual prediction.
